item.title: C# Generated Code Guide
item.description: You should read the proto3 language guide before reading this document. Note The protobuf compiler can generate C# interfaces for definitions using proto2 syntax starting from release 3.10. Refer to the proto2 language guide for details of the semantics of proto2 definitions, and see docs/csharp/proto2.md (view on GitHub) for details on the generated C# code for proto2. Compiler Invocation The protocol buffer compiler produces C# output when invoked with the --csharp_out command-line flag.
